  "prompt": "Are there international laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are international laws and regulations against money laundering. The Financial Action Task Force (FATF) is the primary global organization that sets standards and promotes policies to combat money laundering and terrorist financing. Many countries have implemented anti-money laundering (AML) laws based on FATF recommendations, including:\n\n1. Requirements for financial institutions to verify customer identities\n2. Mandatory reporting of suspicious transactions\n3. Record-keeping regulations\n4. International cooperation in investigating financial crimes\n\nThe United Nations and individual countries also have specific laws and regulations addressing money laundering.",
